Princess Margaret Obaigbena (Nee Usifoh), the mother of chairman of This Newspaper and Arise TV, Nduka Obaigbena, is dead. The Royal family of Owa Kingdom, Delta State announced her passage at 88. Princess Margaret was a former Nursing officer in the former Bendel State Government, which later became Delta State Government.   Apata lauds women’s cricket team despite Kwibuka…     60 women-observers for poll     ‘Prosecute thugs, vote buyers’   She served as Special Adviser to three Delta Governors. She is survived by children, grandchildren and great-grandchildren. A statement by the family said burial arrangements would be announced later.